<article class="content content--reading post">
  <a name="impact"></a>
  <h1>The Impact</h1>

  <p>
    The launch was a success. Clients engaged at high rates, providers valued the clarity of AI-generated topics, and most importantly, the initiative demonstrated that <strong>intersession engagement was not only possible but powerful</strong>. It advanced care quality, supported providers, and created measurable outcomes that Grow could use to strengthen its insurance partnerships.
  </p>

  <p>
    It also set a precedent. Session Topics became the proving ground that validated intersession engagement as a <strong>pillar of Grow Therapy's product vision</strong>, influencing how we would design the mobile app and our long-term strategy.
  </p>

  <a name="reflection"></a>
  <h1>Reflection</h1>

  <p>
    This project was never just about a feature. It was about recognizing when ambition was too small, aligning with leadership to expand scope, coaching a team into deeper exploration, and pushing for bold, innovative ideas backed by evidence. It was about navigating strategic pivots, practicing pragmatism when needed, and still delivering impact.
  </p>

  <p>
    For me, Session Topics was a demonstration of design leadership at its fullest: setting strategy, championing innovation, securing executive alignment, and raising the bar for my team. It showed how design can shape not just the product, but the company's direction.
  </p>
